title: Live AFL trade chat: Don to move?
text:
AFL trade period: Fox Footy’s live chat of exchange period, who changes clubs on day two? Staff writers FOX SPORTS AFL trade period: Fox Footy’s live chat of exchange period, who changes clubs on day two? Staff writers FOX SPORTS Collingwood desperate for Giant Adam Treloar 0:44 
AFL: Collingwood list manager Derek Hine concedes the Pies will need to offer up draft picks if they're to be successful in landing GWS Giants midfielder Adam Treloar October 12th 2015 a day ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
AFTER a massive first day of the trade period, players like Jake Melksham, James Aish and Adam Treloar look to make their moves on day two. 
Melksham looks likely to move to be traded to Melbourne for a second-round draft pick once the exchanges get underway at 9AM. 
Late last night, Brisbane’s Jack Redden was traded to West Coast for a first-round pick (currently pick 17). 
SCROLL DOWN FOR OUR LIVE TRADE CHAT 
The Lions could be involved in another move as James Aish’s situation heats up. 
Collingwood are looking to trade for the young gun midfielder with picks in both 2015 and 2016 on the table for him and GWS Giants midfielder Adam Treloar. Other Stories
